This paper presents a novel end-to-end network for panoptic segmentation, a task related to computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new propagation mechanism for panoptic logits, which could be relevant to natural language processing and text analysis, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper presents results on the Cityscapes and COCO datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia and computer graphics research, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
